article.headline: William & Mary 71, James Madison 56
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Adam Payton scored 18 points and Peter Stein scored 17 as William and Mary pulled away in the second half to beat James Madison 71-56 Wednesday night. The Tribe (13-11, 6-8 Colonial Athletic Association) scored seven straight points to close the first half and took a 28-22 lead into the locker room at halftime. James Madison (7-17, 4-10) shot just 25 percent in the first half, but kept it close through free throw shooting. William and Mary shot 76.2 percent in the second to expand their lead to as much as 18, and the Dukes weren't able to threaten. The Tribe's Nathan Mann scored 14 and David Schneider had 11. Terrance Carter scored 26 and Joe Poesy added 10 for James Madison.
